	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=13&mid=98781280049145>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=98781280049145>RE: Spells in melee</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=98781280049145#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Apr 20th 8:26 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Well, Well, Well.<br>We sure have had alot of interesting views on this subject.<br><br>I have written an earlier view, and now it is time for one more.<br><br>1st. Don't solo a dungeon like the Warrens at your level.(To agro, not worth it)<br><br>2nd. If you are in a high agro area, fight in a group of tanks and healers.<br><br>3rd. If using a pet, always kill the weak and keep the strong, no matter how much tiny daggers you use.(Never go into the field with less then 2 stacks of tiny daggers period!)<br>** Always check your pets life with one quick click of the mouse, then target the mob back by hitting your F-8 key**<br>** Tank for your pet when you have to**<br><br>4th. At level 12 you will get charm, use it!<br><br>5th. Be patient, be incognito,&nbsp;&nbsp;be aware of your surroundings, use your F-9 key to change views if you have to see what other mobs lurk close by.<br><br>6th. Move your most used spells into your hot keys.<br>When hiting the coresponding number, you will fine that the spells cast alot more quickly and smoothly.<br>It will alow you to constantly press the number untill the spell triggers.<br>You will not have to use your mouse to target that small spell icon while you try to pay attention to the battle.<br>It may take a little while to get used to it, but it is well worth the training.<br>Also use your F-keys, such as F-8 to target the nearest NPC, or F-1 to target your self.<br>This will save you also, I promise.<br><br>7th. If you are going to solo, fight in open areas with a good view of what's coming.<br><br>8th. Don't use your pet in a dungeon, charm an NPC if you have to have a pet.<br>Make sure you have all of your pet hot keys ready before you start charming.( You will need to control your pet.)(This is way better than any animation)<br><br>9th. Time your spells.<br>Watch your screen, and watch for misses.<br><br>10th. The most important thing of all.<br>Have fun, you will die many times, it's all part of growing in the game.<br>Learn from your mistakes and triumphs.<br>Always be willing to help someone when they need it, for they may be the one helping you at your time of need.<br>Be safe, patient and aware.<br>Don't take a risk or gamble, unless you can aford to deal with the reprecutions.<br><br>Play Smarter not Harder.<br>Enjoy<br><br>Zoidicus.<br>  <br></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
