	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=380><span id=Scholar>Cubwynn</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>67 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.01]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Stat jewelry is always a good thing to invest in (and that not because I'm a jeweler *giggle*). At lower levels you should concentrate on getting CHA jewelery especially, to make those mezzes and stuns work. A pair of Electrum Cat's Eye Agate bracers (+4 CHA each, approx 4pp each) and a Silver Cat's Eye Agate Necklace (+3 CHA, 2-3pp) is a good, CHEAP investment for a young Enchanter. <br><br>As far as armor goes, try auctioning for Raw Silk, or make it yourself!! It's fairly easy to raise Tailoring skill if you're in one of the newbie areas over-run with spiderlings (Steamfont, Greater Faydark, North Ro), or spiders (Butcherblock, East/West Commons, West/North Karana). Check out one of the tailoring guides here or at Caster's Realm. You can also auction to buy Damask or Gossimer armor, both good choices for a young Enchanter.<br><br>I've forgetton to ask whether you had journeyed to Highkeep Hold to get your level 8/12 pet spells. Always make sure you have your best pet up!<br><br>Cubwynn Payne<br>High Elven Enchanter of the 30th Mezz<br>Ordo Ursi Prismatus<br>Lanys T'vyl</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
