	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=380><span id=Scholar>Cubwynn</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>67 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.97]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Fiddo is right... once you get level 16 Mesmerization it's much easy to control the situation. Have everyone assist the puller and beat each one down one by one. Make sure you're far enough away that you don't get caught in your own AoE Mezz, though.<br><br>If your purpose is going to be in a group, ditch the pet. You will die VERY quickly.<br><br>Since the original post was from a necromancer, here are some tips to sorting these things out. These are also good tips for an Enchanter of any age that can't or doesn't want to use an AoE spell.<br><br>You can always move in closer and hope you can resolve the group of MOBs from one blob to individuals. But when you are doing this, make sure you don't actually get into melee range, or you'll have any extras pounding on you instead of the tank! You can also try switching to an overhead view (hit F9 until you get there), as that seems to be the easiest way to tell MOBs apart. If all else fails, /assist the tank and see which MOB's name starts flashing... it's crude, but in some situations, that's the only way to tell them apart.<br><br>Good luck!<br><br>Cubwynn Payne<br>High Elven Enchanter of the 30th Glamour<br>Ordo Ursi Prismatus<br>Lanys T'vyl</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
