	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Amen to the Overhead view!&nbsp;&nbsp;and in groups lose the pet.  I have found that as an<br>enchanter the two spells that help here are mez and charm...  Using the overhead<br>view with attack off, outside melee range find which baddie the tank is hittin on.  <br>Target another one and charm him, reassist and /pet attack.  Then Mez any other<br>baddie out there.  Be aware that the Pet will attack you when the Charm wears off<br>so make sure your Charisma is high and pay attention to the killing as you want <br>the charmed pet to tank for you as much as possible.  Working the Orc Highway<br>with a savvy group, we have taken on up to 5 very red Orcs in a row with no<br>deaths using this technique.  It requires good cooperation from the group but can<br>be very sucessful.  Tellar on Drinal and E'ci Servers.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
