	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=28996><span id= >ekralc</span></a><br><span id=notbold>3 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Everone has covered the mezz plans very well. So i will address a few good uses for the pet. First just because it is so important....Never use your pet in a dungeon!<br>When to use a pet in a group?0ne is for reverse kiting with a druid or necro or ranger, they snare, you MR defuff( makes them real mad) and then Dot, you get hit once or twice before you get away( you Best have SOW).&nbsp;&nbsp;Now just nuke and run, The baddy chases you, your pets and tanks kill it. Fear kitting works well, but with an orgaized small group(2-3), having the mobs chase you is very efficent.<br><br>The more important reason to use your pet is for a safty net in a group you do not know(or just playing with tacticly challenged friends). But you must have sow up for the safty pet to work. here is an example.<br>1. your puller pulls three instead of one.<br>2. you mezz one incoming. <br>3. you mezz one in battle... but alas your group are not assisting the puller(or the assist failed, which does happen). wack the mob is unmezzed and tick off at YOU.<br>4. hit u befor a remezz can be caste. pet is in fight<br>5. run a tight circle aruound gruop so you are still in healing range.<br>6. you pet will get that mob of you very quickly. <br>7. mezz the other, if it is rested try again, <br>7. while you pet is getting pounded into the dirt you move to other side of group and wait to remezz.<br><br>The above steps are for groups you do not trust, or have not gained your trust yet.<br>When you have there trust, practice your charm instead.. it wil help in the higher lvls.<br>45 lvl selrahc Brellis</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
