	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=43653><span id=Scholar>GLASS</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>202 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I've read this whole string of posts and I'm not going to disagree and say that you all don't have a good point, HOWEVER it's not just tanks and there are tanks out there that understand and greatly appreciate the role of the enchanter.&nbsp;&nbsp;In fact, after my first group with one I decided that would be the next class I play.<br><br>My main is a monk, puller/tank.  The first time I played with a chanter I had no idea what mez was and I was the one who broke it.  Immediately after I did, I realized it was a mistake and didn't do it again.  Since that experience I have always made a point to pick up or suggest to the group to pick up a chanter who needs work.<br><br>On the other hand, I've played with several people who didn't know what they were doing or how best to play their class, and yes one of them was an enchanter.  I noticed he was playing with a pet which I understand is generally not a good idea for chanters in a group setting.  Perhaps that was his downfall.  I've also played with wizzys who overnuke and get slaughtered very quickly, druids who repeatedly aggro mobs and then run around in circles waiting for the tanks to pull them off, and hybrids that insist on pulling then get mad when they overpull and get killed before we can pull the mobs off of them.<br><br>Basically, there are some players out there who are better than others and who know their jobs and the jobs of others well.  I try to stay humble enough to realize that I know very little about most of the classes out there still have a lot to learn.  In the meanwhile I play my class the best I know how and try to help the whole group out how ever I can.  And I like to think this will pay off in the long run by giving myself a good name amongst good players to group with in the future.<br><br>Well that's it for my rant today.  Thanks for listening and good gaming!<br><br>Zasshatiz - Iksar Monk<br>Circle of Radiance Guild<br>Luclin Server</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
