	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=13&mid=98452480829467>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=98452480829467>RE: how do i enchant items?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=98452480829467#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Tue, Mar 13th 6:06 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=1706><span id= >Laleini</span></a><br><span id=notbold>33 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.93]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Ok, what you have to do is buy a jewelery kit, it looks like a little bag. You go to the jewelery shop and buy silver bars. You click on one and hold it, then cast the spell enchant silver, while it's in your hand. Then put it in the jewelers kit and put a gem in with it, pres combine and see what turns out. Sometimes it will make something, sometimes it won't depending on how good your skill is. You should start by putting as many practice points into jewel craft as you can, then you start with silver and malachite. Go to castersrealm and get a trivial chart, which tells you what to mix with what according to your skill level. What server do you play on? If you need help I play on Fennin Ro as Laleini Windsong, send me a tell in game.<br></p>&nbsp;<br>Laleini Windsong <br>Enchantress Extroadinare</td></td></tr>
