	     </form></table><tr><td colspan=2><ul><table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99195946947158>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=13&mid=99195946947158>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=99195946947158>RE: New Enchanter Needs Help</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=99195946947158#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Jun 7th 8:17 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=50451><span id=Scholar>riotgirl</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>54 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Bah! I must have swapped personalities with Pusbag for a moment or two.<br><br>There is -no- real hard and fast method towards rising fast simply because despite all of the various strategies informing you of how to make x number of levels in x amount of time, those people who wrote those strategies are:<br><br>(1) Players who have an indepth knowledge of the game and their class<br>(2) Bragging<br>(3) Bragging and twinked<br>(4) Sprouting useless information<br><br>These strategies work because the players who write them understand both their class and their abilities well enough to be able to use them. Some of them will be mines of information; others will be next to useless.<br><br>The strategies that you -should- follow are those that clearly explain the reasoning and thinking behind their strategy i.e. what the goal behind the strategy is, the method that they used to achieve the strategy as well as explaining the various tactics to provide you with a -better- understanding of how to use your spells effectively.<br><br>Constructive advice: visit eqcastersrealm.com to read up on your level 4 spells. In particular, colour flux, mesmorise, and tashan. Although, you will still be meleeing with the occasional DoT thrown in, you can start to become a little more effective once you obtain the above spells.<br><br>If you are in Greater Faydark, you should be able to kill decaying skeletons and orc pawns with greater ease once you have the -basic- idea of what your level 4 spells do (go visit eqcastersrealm.com and re-read all the posts in this here forum). If you are feeling -brave- then you could travel to Steamfront -- through Lesser Faydark, an extremely dangerous area -- to kill Kobolds. They drop cloth armour as well as various bags, including backpacks. <br><br>Note: before travelling to new areas, always read up on the zones on Allakhazams as well as EQ Atlas(provides maps). I would advise BB mountains from around level 6 rather than the interminable Orc Hill. If you can find a group, Giant Scarabs are quite good exp I've found -- also, unlike Skeletons and Orc Centurions, they do -not- bash i.e. stun. Yes, they occasionally hit hard but that is where 'enfeeblement' kicks in (debuff spell). <br><br>Read up on Steamfront and ButcherBlock Mountains <br>(both a zone or two away) -- ButcherBlock is the safer of the two locations due to the various guard houses dotted around the path. Yes, I do -like- ButcherBlock :)<br><br>Skill points: To be honest, save 'em. For the simple reason that nearly EVERY skill can be raised through repeatative use if you have just 1 point in that particular skill. Newbie advice would be to stick 5 skill points at first level in either 1hand blunt or piercing, as this will allow you to hit mobs a much better, and should help you level faster.<br><br>When you get to level 4, put just -one- point into meditate (skill which will help you regenerate Mana faster when resting) -- meditate is an extremely easy skill to max out at every level; hence the necessity of -only- placing 1 skill point to learn the skill.<br><br>The -best- advice I can give you is to gain an indepth knowledge of your starting continent, be that Faydwer or Antonica. Read the forums on the particular zones next to your starting zone, and use EQ Atlas for examining maps for location references.<br><br>Read and re-read the majority of the posts placed in this forum. <br><br>riotgirl<br>(12 seasons fledgling Enchanter)<br>Ayonae Ro server</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
