<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99194232445200>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=13&mid=99194232445200>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=99194232445200>RE: New Enchanter Needs Help</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=99194232445200#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Jun 7th 3:32 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=50451><span id=Scholar>riotgirl</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>54 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>&lt;shakes head&gt; Whenever I read a post that is a disguised plea to be powerlevelled, I suggest to the poster that perhaps they choose a class that is better suited to how they would like to play EQ.<br><br>An enchanter requires MUCH patience and plenty of practice before you even -start- to become comfortable with the class. It was only when I struggled through the hellish level 8, and the tough level 9 to reach 10th, that I begun to appreciate the versatility of our class. If you wish to rush through the difficult levels then you are merely creating a mediocre character that will -repeatedly- fail you at the higher levels. There is a personality characterisitic that you must develop: 'foresight'. Please develop it. If not stick to Clerics or Warriors.<br><br>Gosh! That was a little harsh, wasn't it? Actually, if you are having difficulty and/or are getting bored at level 3 (!?) then clearly playing an Enchanter is not the class for you. <br><br>There is a -very- good reason as to why the newbie levels exist over and beyond the learning curve. You -must- max your spell classes at EVERY level. Each spell belongs to a particular spell class i.e. the 'Colour Flux' series of spells belongs to the Diviniation spell class.<br><br>Melee/spell skills are capped by level I believe (please inform me if there are any gross inaccuracies contained wherein). The formula is as follows:<br><br>Level*5 +5<br>Hence, for level 3, the skill cap would be:<br>3*5= 15, +5= 20.<br><br>Your skill levels define the effectiveness of your skills/spells from that particular class. Hence, if you wish to see your spells fizzling all the time, then by all means, powerlevel yourself to mediocrity. The -smart- player will take an hour or so at each level to max out their skills for that particular level: i.e. Sense Heading; various spell classes e.g. Alteration, Abjuration, Diviniation and Conjuration, being the most important. If you hope to use the mesmorisation line of spells then be -sure- to max out Conjuration each and every level; swimming, if you are so inclined! <br><br>Maxing out spell levels is a -good- reason to invest in a animation (pet). Summon said animation, and begin to cast spells from various spell groups (best to be methodical, and raise each and every spell group one at a time) on your docile, placid pet.<br><br>Yes, this can become rather tiresome but -will- make your enchanter a better one rather than a mediocre one. EQ is fairly unforgiving, and mediocrity is rapidly weeded out. Heh, or at least, you'll never find a -decent- group (c.f. 'mediocrity').<br><br>Note: At level 3 there is not -much- else to kill other than low level mobs. If you wish another path to power, than perhaps try the various quests for your particular zone.<br><br>I too, become bored of endless CB raids, and although it is not particularly efficient if one wishes to rise up in levels at the lowest downtime, I generally explore other zones, indulge in my trade skills, as well as idle conversation. There is -so- much to be curious about and explore. All depends on your motivation. If gaining levels and power motivates you, then read the various guides which promise quick success to power.<br><br>Remember: the most -important- element in EQ is 'motivation' (as in life). If a particular facet of the game does not stimulate you, then you will rapidly and disillusioned unless you try something ELSE &lt;gasps!&gt; which will excite you once more.<br><br>riotgirl<br>(12 seasons fledging Enchanter)<br>Ayonae Ro server</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
